cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV. 

The paper investigates the properties and performance of stable recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning for sequence tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the approximation of stable recurrent networks by feed-forward networks, which relates to the sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
